The first thing to check is whether or not your arc file is valid, or
perhaps has some form of gzip corruption.

What is the output of:

  $ gzip -t /home/attabi/essai/IAH-20121230204825-00000-blackbook.arc.gz

If gzip says that the file is a valid gzip file, then there are other
things to investigate.  However, if the gzip validation test reports an
error, then your arc file is corrupted and the message you are seeing
from NutchWAX is most likely reporting that it encountered the corrupted
part.


Aaron
